Package gov.nih.nci.cabig.caaers.web.fields Description

Goal

Provides an object model for HTML form fields. Fields are aggregated into tab definitions using the TabWithFields Tab subclass. Modeling & aggregating form fields this way makes it easy to a) move fields between tabs by making changes in a single place and b) avoid boilerplate HTML in the tabs' views. The base interface is InputField.

Design

InputFields are divided into categories. The implementation of aggregation (see RepeatingFieldGroupFactory and CompositeField) involves several wrapper classes. For this reason, there is not one implementation per category, with specialized behavior in each category-implementing class. (If it were implemented so, there would need to be a new subclass for each category for each distinct type of wrapping.)

Instead, there is a main class DefaultInputField and a factory InputFieldFactory. Specialized per-category properties are stored in the attributes map for the field. Known keys for the attributes are defined in InputField itself. InputFieldAttributes provides type-safe helpers for setting the known attributes.
